.TH "pcm_open" 9 "pcm_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcm_open \- implements open callback function for PCM middle layer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pcm_open
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
pointer to ALSA PCM substream
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is called when a PCM substream is opened. At least, the function should
initialize the runtime->hw record.

Returns 0 on success or error code otherwise.
